  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "aq5FP6Q80FdPlhvPzY0pzZhJHoc=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "Document editors in Powerhouse are React components following a component-based architecture:\n\n- `editor.tsx` - Main editor wrapper (entry point)\n- Container component (e.g., `TodoList.tsx`) - Orchestrates child components, reads state via hook\n- List component (e.g., `Todos.tsx`) - Renders collections\n- Item component (e.g., `Todo.tsx`) - Individual items with edit/delete\n- Form component (e.g., `AddTodo.tsx`) - Handles new item creation\n\nStyling options:\n1. **Default HTML styling** - Standard tags render with boilerplate styles\n2. **Tailwind CSS** - Built into Connect, use utility classes directly\n3. **Custom CSS files** - Import traditional .css files\n\nPattern details:\n- Use `useSelectedTodoListDocument()` hook for state + dispatch in any component\n- Import action creators from generated code\n- Use React local state (`useState`) for UI-only state (e.g., `isEditing` toggle)\n- Use document dispatch for persistent data changes\n- Built-in actions like `setName` from `document-model/document` for document metadata\n- `DocumentToolbar` component from design system provides standard document actions",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:34.000Z"
    }
  },
